  "text": "The 1 −− state ψ(4160) is commonly identified with the 2 3 D 1 state. The average experimental mass and width from the PDG are M = 4191 ± 5 MeV and Γ = 70 ± 10 MeV, respectively [CITATION_1] , which are consistent with linear potential model predictions. However, with a screened potential, the predicted mass for ψ 1 (2D) is about 100 MeV smaller than the observation. The ψ 1 (2D) resonance can decay into χ cJ (1P)γ and χ cJ (2P)γ via the radiative transitions.",
